Family and friends have paid tribute to a young man who became trapped between a railway platform and a train after a fight broke out at the station.

Ryan Harrison died when he became stuck between the platform edge and the train as it moved away.

It is understood that following a row with a group of men, Mr Harrison either fell or was pushed down the side of the platform next to a stationary train.

The 22-year-old is thought to have been with a male friend at the station when the pair became involved in a confrontation with a group of men.

